AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - EUROPE (09): LATVIA (KRASLAVA), POLAND (PODLASKIE), UPDATE
********************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this posting:
[1] Latvia (Kraslava): domestic pig, wild boar
[2] Poland (Podlaskie): wild boar

******
[1] Latvia (Kraslava): domestic pig, wild boar
Date: Fri 4 Jul 2014
Source: Latvian Food and Veterinary Office (PVD/FVO) press release [in Latvian, machine trans., summ., edited]
http://www.pvd.gov.lv/lat/augj_izvlne/aktualittes/pvd_pieaug_afrikas_cuku_mera_a


Yesterday, 3 Jul 2014, late in the evening, PVD received laboratory test results confirming African swine fever (ASF) virus in one domestic swine and one wild boar.

According to Kraslava regional veterinarian, the owner of the animals shed had kept 2 fattening pigs, from one of which the ASF virus was laboratory confirmed. The animals were kept in outdoor pens.

The infected wild boar was found in the Kraslava municipality close to the border.

Thus, up to the present date [4 Jul 2014], the ASF virus has been confirmed in 13 wild boars and 4 domestic pigs.

--
