[Latvia has reported to the OIE a total of 6 ASF outbreaks, both in the Kraslava municipality, since the start of the event on 26 Jun 2014. The last follow-up report (No. 2) was submitted on 3 Jul 2014.

See the reports and an interactive map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=15485. - Mod.AS]

******
[2] Poland (Podlaskie): wild boar
Date: Tue 8 Jul 2014
Source: Rosselkhoznadzor (Russian Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance) News [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
http://fsvps.ru/fsvps/news/10370.html


About new outbreaks of African swine fever in Poland
----------------------------------------------------
Disease outbreaks have been registered in pigs in Sokol and Byalostokskom, within the Podlaskie voivodship [Poland is divided into 16 voivodships, primary subdivisions]. The diagnosis was confirmed in the European Union Reference Laboratory for African swine fever. To date [8 Jul 2014], 6 ASF outbreaks have officially been registered in Poland.

Rosselhoznadzor has repeatedly warned the European Commission about the need to depopulate wild boars in Poland in view of the risk of ASF introduction and its spread from Poland to Germany, the Czech Republic and Austria.

--
